rom the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born in 1378, in Stiffkey, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She married William Ermingland about 1399, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1434, in her hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1378–1434":"1378–1434","1374–1482":"1374–1482","1404–1478":"1404–1478","1408–Male":"1408–Surnud","1404":"1404","about 1408":"umbes 1408","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1378":"1378","1374":"1374","1482":"1482","about 1399":"umbes 1399","1408":"1408","Stiffkey, Norfolk, England":"Stiffkey, Norfolk, England","Stiffkey, Norfolk, , England":"Stiffkey, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"1378–1434":"1378–1434","1374–1482":"1374–1482","1404–1478":"1404–1478","1408–Male":"1408–Kuollut","1404":"1404","about 1408":"noin 1408","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1378":"1378","1374":"1374","1482":"1482","about 1399":"noin 1399","1408":"1408","Stiffkey, Norfolk, England":"Stiffkey, Norfolk, England","Stiffkey, Norfolk, , England":"Stiffkey, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"1378–1434":"1378–1434","1374–1482":"1374–1482","1404–1478":"1404–1478","1408–Male":"1408–Décédé","1404":"1404","about 1408":"environ 1408","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1378":"1378","1374":"1374","1482":"1482","about 1399":"environ 1